name: Verify the fuel types as filter for Store locator functionality

steps.name: I check that the "Welcome Screen" is displayed
I click on "GET STARTED" button
I check that the "Choose Data Preferences Screen" is displayed
I click on "ALLOW ALL TRACKING" button
I check that the "First SignIn Screen" is displayed
I click on "SKIP" button
I check that the "Notification Permission Screen" is displayed
I click on "CONTINUE" button
I check that the "Location Permission Flow Screen" is displayed
I check that the "Location Permission Flow Screen" is displayed
I click on "CONTINUE" button
I skip linking my card
I check that the "Home Screen" is displayed
I click on "STORES" button
I check that the "Stores Screen" is displayed
I click on "SEARCH BAR" input
I enter the "Denmark" in the "SEARCH BAR" input
I check that the "Search Results Screen" is displayed
I click on "Denmark" search result
I check that the "Stores Screen" is displayed
I click on "SEARCH BAR FILTER" button
I check that the "Filters List Screen" is displayed
I get the text from the "FUELS" label
I check that the application text: "FUELS" is equals to expected value: "FUELS"
I get the text from the "SERVICES" label
I check that the application text: "SERVICES" is equals to expected value: "SERVICES"
I get the text from the "Diesel" fuel type
I check that the application text: "Diesel" is equals to expected value: "Diesel"
I get the text from the "Gasoline 95" fuel type
I check that the application text: "Gasoline 95" is equals to expected value: "Gasoline 95"
I get the text from the "Upgrade 95" fuel type
I check that the application text: "Upgrade 95" is equals to expected value: "Upgrade 95"
I get the text from the "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the application text: "APPLY 0 FILTERS" is equals to expected value: "APPLY 0 FILTERS"
I check that the "Filters List Screen" is displayed
I verify "DIESEL" filter and its "UNCHECKED" state
I verify "GASOLINE_95" filter and its "UNCHECKED" state
I verify "UPGRADE_95" filter and its "UNCHECKED" state
I click on the "DIESEL" filter
I click on the "GASOLINE_95" filter
I verify "DIESEL" filter and its "CHECKED" state
I verify "GASOLINE_95" filter and its "CHECKED" state
I get the text from the "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the application text: "APPLY 2 FILTERS" is equals to expected value: "APPLY 2 FILTERS"
I click on "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the "Stores Screen" is displayed
I click on "SEARCH BAR FILTER" button
I get the text from the "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the application text: "APPLY 2 FILTERS" is equals to expected value: "APPLY 2 FILTERS"
I click on "Close" button
I check that the "Stores Screen" is displayed
I click on "SEARCH BAR FILTER" button
I get the text from the "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the application text: "APPLY 2 FILTERS" is equals to expected value: "APPLY 2 FILTERS"
I click on "CLEAR ALL" button
I get the text from the "APPLY FILTERS" button
I check that the application text: "APPLY 0 FILTERS" is equals to expected value: "APPLY 0 FILTERS"
I click on "Close" button on filters screen
